1
00:00:01,480 --> 00:00:03,000
Rosh Hashanah for me is...

2
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:05,400
It's family, it's...

3
00:00:05,960 --> 00:00:08,280
It's home, it's...
-the best show in town.

4
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:12,600
Way more stressful than "Big Brother,"
way more wild than "Survivor."

5
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:15,360
And way more exhausting than "The Hall of Fame."

6
00:00:15,440 --> 00:00:18,680
But it's okay, I've gotten used to it and...

7
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:20,760
I even enjoy it.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:22,880
Sometimes.

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,400
It's, it's, it's joy,

10
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:32,119
It's a big joy to host the family.

11
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:34,880
Happy New Year, everyone.

12
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:37,000
Yeah.

13
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:41,440
So what, a derby, huh?
-What derby?

14
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,000
My parents against your parents.

15
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:45,160
Honey, why against? Really,

16
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:48,040
It's a family, social, friendly holiday gathering.

17
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,280
I hope you're mentally prepared for this, yeah?
Because it happens every few months.

18
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:53,200
Okay, every time it hits me again.

19
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:55,640
Which grandparents are we visiting today?

20
00:00:55,720 --> 00:00:59,520
Today, honey, it's both grandpas
and both grandmas, all together.

21
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,440
The whole clan.
-What's a clan?

22
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:06,040
A clan is a lot of warm people making a fuss.

23
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:07,520
Funny.

24
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:10,280
I don't get why we always need these
summit meetings during holidays

25
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:11,800
and the extravagant meals.

26
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:14,720
The atmosphere is so tense.
-Is there an accident?

27
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:16,560
No, for heaven's sake, there's no accident.

28
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,760
Not yet.

29
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:22,600
Sorry for the really bad connection,

30
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:24,240
but do you happen to know where your parents are?

31
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:27,560
Another hundred meters at the turn, turn right.

32
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:30,800
It's not at this turn, it's at the next one,
I remember it very well.

33
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:34,560
You and your memory haven't been
on the same page for weeks, Pinhas.

34
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,680
Yeah, well, then tell me, where should I turn?

35
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:39,720
If you had listened to me earlier, you wouldn't be asking now.

36
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:45,880
So now make a legal U-turn
at the nearest roundabout, take the second exit.

37
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:47,600
Mom, you're really G-P-S.

38
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:50,200
Excuse me, I'm way better than GPS, right?

39
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:52,680
Yeah, but you can turn off GPS.

40
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,760
Don't worry, I'll be turned off in the grave.

41
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,240
How do you always end up at the grave?

42
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:00,160
Let me surprise you,

43
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:03,280
in the end, we'll all end up in the grave.

44
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:04,680
Mom, it doesn't matter what they talk about,

45
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:07,600
rising fuel prices, revolutions in the Middle East,

46
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:10,080
in the end, we'll find ourselves at your funeral.

47
00:02:10,639 --> 00:02:12,640
And sooner rather than later.
-Left.

48
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:16,680
No way, there's no left turn here,
do you want to kill us?

49
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:23,000
Okay, so now make a legal U-turn
at the nearest roundabout, take the third exit.

50
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:27,240
If you had listened to me, you'd already be in the middle of the Kiddush.

51
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:28,600
Or the Kaddish.

52
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:35,320
Look at me, look at me and...

53
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,520
Shabbat Shalom...
-Happy Holiday.

54
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,560
Happy Holiday.
-Happy Holiday.

55
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:51,000
Happy New Year, Happy New Year.

56
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,960
Happy Holiday, Happy New Year.

57
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:59,080
Mom, what a dress.
-Thanks.

58
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,160
Well, where are your parents?

59
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,360
They're on their way, I don't know where.

60
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:05,480
Do you think they still remember the way here?

61
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:07,440
Yeah, the truth is they really haven't been here for a while.

62
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:10,480
Yeah, we all forgot what it was like.
-It was tsimmes.

63
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,920
What?
'B', come on, enough already.

64
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:16,680
I'm really happy and excited
that your parents will be here with us.

65
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:19,160
It was Rosh Hashanah!

66
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,000
A holiday...

67
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:25,040
Very important.

68
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:30,280
It symbolizes beginnings,

69
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:34,680
It symbolizes new starts.

70
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:40,840
And as we know, every beginning has an end.

71
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:46,200
And every end has a beginning.
-Grandpa.

72
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:52,800
Every evening has the morning that follows! And then! Afternoon.

73
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:59,520
And then we have evening again
and then we have night and the watch...

74
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:06,080
Soon quietly for the third time.
-Grandpa.

75
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:08,360
I asked about the family.

76
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:09,400
So could you wait a minute

77
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:12,760
because I was just about to talk about the family.

78
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:18,640
We talked about morning, we talked about night, about the watch,

79
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:22,640
Which watch was I?
Now you confused me, please.

80
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,800
Why aren't Shai's parents coming?
-Mom, it's still early,

81
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:27,760
What do you need them stuck here in the living room for?

82
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:28,840
You're right.

83
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,120
They say that...

84
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,240
You don't choose your family.

85
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:35,840
But personally,
if I had the choice,

86
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:41,640
I would choose exactly the same family,
just like it is.

87
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,280
Mom!

88
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,360
Mom, where are you?

89
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:50,640
Well, with slight changes but really slight.

90
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:51,600
Mom!

91
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:54,320
That was a joke, a real joke.

92
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,240
Mom!

93
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,440
Are you here?

94
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Can we erase the last part?

95
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,320
Hey, Silvan,

96
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:06,200
Wouldn't you prefer to skip all these holidays?

97
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:10,240
I gain at least ten percent every holiday.

98
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:12,640
Are those ten percent from your knees or your belly?

99
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,880
Oh, I would skip all these holidays,

100
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:23,680
There's just too much family overload, you know?

101
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:28,800
It's like a pile of holidays all together

102
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:33,240
when each holiday separately... it's really a disaster,

103
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,720
It's something! There's nothing to be done.

104
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:41,480
All you have to do
is just set your time back

105
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:47,640
and hope with all your heart that in two hours
everyone will leave already...

106
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:54,040
To that, they'll go, they'll all go home.

107
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:58,760
Just to be clear,

108
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:04,600
your parents are very, very welcome here.
-Of course.

109
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:06,840
We're just talking hypothetically.
-Yeah.

110
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,880
Also about skipping the holidays,

111
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:12,120
we're only talking theoretically, right?
-Yeah.

112
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:14,880
Because look at me, what,
do you see me skipping any holiday?

113
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:18,000
I'll be honest with you,
I can't imagine you skipping at all.

114
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,320
That's what I...

115
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,880
Do you remember Shai's brother is coming, Adam, right?
Keep that in mind?

116
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:28,680
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom, babe.

117
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,520
Shabbat shalom, my sweet.

118
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,360
And here’s mine.
-What... white.

119
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:35,240
I'm dressed for the holiday, yeah.
-Fits perfectly with the table.

120
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:40,560
If Adam is coming,
then I need one more chair and one more plate.

121
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,720
Is Shai's brother coming too?
-Yeah. Why, what's the problem?

122
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,560
There's no problem, quite the opposite, it's a big problem.

123
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:48,360
I meant it! I dressed up for Rosh Hashanah.
-Really?

124
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:51,280
I need to change the whole concept.
-Meirav, Meirav, relax, Adam is family, okay?

125
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:53,160
Do you remember what happened the last time they met, at the K?

126
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,960
The concept stays the same, holiday.

127
00:06:56,960 --> 00:07:00,000
Excuse me, I'm disappearing from here
and forget you saw me like this.

128
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:06,800
Meirav gets anxious during the holidays,
so she feels the loneliness more intensely.

129
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:10,880
It's okay, Mom, sooner or later
she'll find the one who's right for her.

130
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,680
Yeah, sooner or later it won't happen.

131
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,560
It's not good for man to be alone, right?

132
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:20,200
This man is exactly the one I need.

133
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:23,840
I have a strong feeling it's him for a long time.

134
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:29,120
He has everything I need
in a life partner and vice versa,

135
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:32,600
He doesn't have anything I don't need in a partner.

136
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,360
Shabbat Shalom.

137
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:36,520
Have a good Shabbat.
-Shabbat Shalom.

138
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,480
Have a good Shabbat.

139
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,760
Have a good Shabbat.
-What a fool I am.

140
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,400
Have a good Shabbat, Silvan.

141
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:43,360
What's with this camera? Are you filming?

142
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,800
What, do you have stage fright?

143
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:49,680
I don't have stage fright,
I have a fear of light, music, and everything.

144
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:53,240
The girl needs to submit a project
at school about the family.

145
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,760
The whole family needs to help.

146
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,880
She asked if she could
come film some family stuff here.

147
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:59,240
Of course, what’s the big deal? There's family everywhere today.

148
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,120
Sure, sure, go ahead.

149
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,480
You see? So you can film whatever you want.

150
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:05,080
Your parents won't mind?
-No, no, what...

151
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,600
Not at all. They don't care about anything.

152
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:10,440
By the way, Moshe googled a bit about your dad,
I didn't know he was the Minister of Justice.

153
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:12,360
He's not.
-What do you mean he's not?

154
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,360
Pinchas Rosen, right?

155
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:18,880
That area looks familiar to me.

156
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,400
Should I call Shai?

157
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:23,080
I'm telling you, my mom will get mad.

158
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:27,160
Son, honey, if you don't call, she'll get mad too, right?

159
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:31,000
That's your mom. It's like playing
Russian roulette with all the bullets in.

160
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,280
She'll get mad.

161
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,480
Come on, just call now.

162
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,559
I'm driving, what’s that?

163
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,680
Hello, Dad.
-Yeah, we're on our way, Shai.

164
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:46,720
Don't talk without a hands-free,

165
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:50,200
it's a 1,000 shekel fine and points.
-Okay, okay, hand me Mom.

166
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:56,000
Shai, I told you a thousand times,
don't talk to Dad while he's driving.

167
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:58,680
Did I say it or not?
-You said, you said.

168
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:00,240
He refuses to switch to hands-free.

169
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:03,280
Ask them where they are.
-Mom, I just wanted... where are you?

170
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:06,240
We're in the car, where else could we be?

171
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,560
They're in the car, where could they be?

172
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,920
Yeah, but where's the car?

173
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:13,960
Where's the car located?
-He insists on knowing where we are.

174
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:16,000
Adam, try to read a sign.

175
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:20,560
We don't recognize anything here.
Not the surroundings, not the architecture,

176
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:23,680
We're not used to coming
to these parts of the city at all.

177
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:25,760
Oh, what, did you get lost, Mom?

178
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:29,400
No, no, Shai, it's this place
that got lost, not us.

179
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,920
I have an idea, bring me Adam.
-Okay, hold on.

180
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,240
Take Shai.

181
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,800
Ah, bro.
Bro, thanks, I really owe you one.

182
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:42,640
You can bring them.
-Are you sure? You can still change your mind.

183
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,680
No, forget it, we've kept them waiting long enough.

184
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,160
It's family, in an hour and a half it's over.

185
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:52,640
Wow, how did I not notice, oh man,
well, what a fool I am, bye.

186
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:55,000
What? What did you not notice?

187
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:56,560
On my phone. There's GPS.

188
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:57,800
Why didn't you say anything?

189
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:02,280
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom.

190
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:05,040
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom.

191
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,360
Shabbat shalom. Everyone, please pay attention,

192
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:12,520
How come she said Shabbat shalom
and not Shabbat shalom like all of you?

193
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:13,760
Please.

194
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,240
Why specifically?

195
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,680
Because you...

196
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,000
Me, when I met Mav,

197
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:27,920
I don't know what it means
that he comes from a family like that...

198
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:30,600
With a lot of people.

199
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:32,720
You mean a lot of people.
-No, sweetie,

200
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:35,120
A lot of people like a centipede.

201
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:37,080
When are your parents coming, Shai?
-What?

202
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:40,320
Yeah, they're on their way, running a bit late, they had some...

203
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,160
Confusion on the way.

204
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:44,400
Oh man, I'm starving.

205
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:47,480
Wow, and there are all those blessings beforehand.

206
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:49,920
Hungry.

207
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:53,840
Family is like a stew,
but for Rosh Hashanah, not for Passover.

208
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:56,920
You throw a ton of stuff in a pot,
put it on low heat,

209
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:57,960
and in the end, something comes out of it.

210
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:01,320
When you choose to start a family with someone,

211
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:05,600
you bring your family into the mix,
the one you grew up with,

212
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:07,680
and he kind of brings his family.

213
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:11,160
And really, you know, everyone comes from different backgrounds

214
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:14,560
from families that God forbid, we don't want to know troubles.

215
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:19,960
And together you want to create something
really new, a new family

216
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:24,200
that's like a better version
of the previous one he came from.

217
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:28,120
Happy holiday.
-Hello, happy holiday.

218
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,040
Happy holiday, happy holiday.

219
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,680
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom and sweet.

220
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:32,840
Shabbat shalom.

221
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:35,960
Shabbat shalom, Shabbat shalom, it's been a while since we saw each other.

222
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:39,280
Happy holiday, Shabbat shalom.
-It's been a long, long time since we saw each other, yeah.

223
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,200
Happy holiday.
-Shabbat shalom.

224
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:44,920
Do you remember Meni and Alin?
-Of course.

225
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,200
And Orna and Moshe.

226
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,040
Come on
`let's go

227
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:51,640
It still gets to me.

228
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:55,640
Meirav, hello, how you've grown.

229
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:58,400
Shabbat shalom.
-Shabbat shalom.

230
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:05,440
I'm really happy we have the chance
to come here, to the Hasson family,

231
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,800
and celebrate the holiday with them.

232
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:12,200
Holidays are always a wonderful time for gatherings.

233
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:16,000
Here, we are always welcomed warmly

234
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:22,760
and in every gathering like this, we learn something
about you, about your customs,

235
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,600
it's so exotic.

236
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:26,840
Rachel, this is from me,

237
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:30,280
Not from me, from me.

238
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:32,560
Really, you didn't have to.

239
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:35,200
I know, but I never
come empty-handed.

240
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:40,080
We're a close family, we don't need gifts.

241
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:43,440
